The nm-applet (network manager icon) fails to start when archlinux is defined as a template-vm:
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

In fact
/etc/dbus-1/system.d/org.freedesktop.\ `NetworkManager? </wiki/NetworkManager>`__.conf
does not allow a standard user to run network manager clients. To allow
this, one need to change inside <policy context="default">:

.. code:: wiki

    <deny send_destination="org.freedesktop.NetworkManager"/>

to

.. code:: wiki

    <allow send_destination="org.freedesktop.NetworkManager"/>

